---
title: HelloFresh Turkey Katsu Curry
description: As you can imagine, down at the Fresh Farm, lunch is a pretty big deal. We all sit around our long table and discuss our lunch decisions; the hands-down HelloFresh favourite lunch is undeniably the Katsu Curry (Elliot once managed to eat two and a half in one sitting!). In light of this HelloFresh obsession, Mimi decided to recreate a version for our lovely customers. Enjoy!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/56bb29d6fd2cb9551a8b4568.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/56bb29d6fd2cb9551a8b4568.pdf
time required: 40 minutes
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Japanese
nutrition:
  calories: 771 kcal
  fat: 13 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 116 g
  protein: 37 g
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/hellofresh-turkey-katsu-curry-56bb29d6fd2cb9551a8b4568
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Cut your @onion{1} in half through the root, peel and slice into thin half moon
shapes. Peel and finely chop your @garlic{2%cloves}. Peel your @carrots{2}, cut
them in half lengthways and then chop into half moon shapes about 1cm wide.

Add @oil{1%tbsp} to a #saucepan{} on medium heat and throw in your onion. Cook
for ~{6%minutes} before adding in your chopped garlic, carrots, @salt{1/4%tsp}
and a good grind of @pepper{}. Cook for a further ~{5%minutes}.

Bring @water{350%ml} to the boil in a #pot{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} in preparation
for your rice.

When your carrots have been cooking for ~{5%minutes}, add in your
@curry powder mix{3/4%tsp} and @flour{1%tbsp} and cook for ~{1%minute} before
adding @water{300%ml} and @chicken stock pot{1/2} along with your @honey{1%tbsp}
and @soy sauce{1.5%tbsp}. Stir continuously and bring to a simmer, then leave
to cook for ~{10-15%minutes}, then take off the heat, put a lid on, and leave
to the side until everything else is ready.

In the meantime, add your @basmati rice{1} to your boiling water, put the lid on
and cook for ~{10%minutes} before taking the pot off the heat and leaving for a
further ~{10%minutes}.

> Tip: Don't take the lid off the pot until the whole 20 mins is up!

While the sauce and rice are cooking, prepare your turkey. Put your
@British turkey steaks{2} in between two sheets of #clingfilm{} and bash them
with a #rolling pin{}, until they are 1cm thick.

Put your @crème fraîche{1} in one #bowl{} and give it a quick stir to loosen it
up. Put your @panko breadcrumbs{4%tbsp} in another bowl with @salt{1/4%tsp} and
a good grind of @pepper{}. Coat your bashed turkey steaks first in the
crème fraîche then in the breadcrumbs. Add @oil{2%tbsp} to a #frying pan{} on
medium heat and when the pan is hot, place your turkey steaks in the pan. Cook
for ~{6%minutes} on one side before turning over and cooking for
~{5%minutes} on the other side. Then remove the pan from the heat.

> Tip: The turkey is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Serve the rice in #bowls{} with a spoonful of curry sauce on top. Cut your
turkey into slices about 2cm wide and pop them on top. Voila!